text: _-_ text Ozaki Hiroshi@ __ time 0 _-_ text                                                     USING TEMPLATES@ __ time 0 _-_ text This is a template that configures three tracks for a jazz trio.  General MIDI patches are used.  The Pan parameter is used to create a traditional seating arrangement.@ __ time 0 _-_ text                                                   USING KEY+ OFFSETS@ __ time 0 _-_ text Some instruments are traditionally notated transposed to a different key and/or octave than they sound.  This effect can be accomplished in Cakewalk through use of the Track view Key+ parameter.  For example// the tenor saxophone Key+ should be set to -14@ __ time 0 _-_ text With the Key+ parameter set// the notes you see in all the Cakewalk views and the notes you play will be in the transposed key.  The notes you hear during playback and via MIDI Thru will be in the normal// untransposed key.  This is natural if you are ente@ __ time 0 _-_ text                                            NOT USING THE KEY+ OFFSETS@ __ time 0 _-_ text If you prefer to develop the instrument's part in the normal// untransposed key// you may wish to set the Key+ to 0.  If you do this// then the notation in the Staff view will not be transposed in the traditional way.
